hh3cRpr.name: hh3cRpr
hh3cRpr.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cRpr.description: This MIB manages RPR(Resilient Packet Ring)interfaces by providing an operational table which controls parameters of each RPR interface and reports alarm conditions. A RPR ring is composed of two fiber rings: Outer and Inner.

Hh3cRprRingletID.name: Hh3cRprRingletID
Hh3cRprRingletID.description: Indicates the path on which data flow is selected. The valid value is ringlet0 and ringlet1. They indicate two RPR fiber rings. Ringlet0 refers to outer ring and ringlet1 refers to inner ring.
Hh3cRprRingletID.reference: IEEE 802.17 V3.3 Subclause 11.2.1.1 Span and ringlet parameterization.

Hh3cRprServiceClass.name: Hh3cRprServiceClass
Hh3cRprServiceClass.description: Indicates the service class of RPR. The valid value is ClassC, ClassB, ClassA1 and ClassA0.

hh3cRprMaxmumDefineTable.name: hh3cRprMaxmumDefineTable
hh3cRprMaxmumDefineTable.description: This table contains the specs of RPR ring.

hh3cRprMaxmumDefineEntry.name: hh3cRprMaxmumDefineEntry
hh3cRprMaxmumDefineEntry.description: The entry of RPR Maximum Table.

hh3cRprMaxMumIfIndex.name: hh3cRprMaxMumIfIndex
hh3cRprMaxMumIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of this RPR interface.

hh3cRprMaxStationNumDefine.name: hh3cRprMaxStationNumDefine
hh3cRprMaxStationNumDefine.description: Max station number supported by RPR ring.

hh3cRprMaxReservedRateDefine.name: hh3cRprMaxReservedRateDefine
hh3cRprMaxReservedRateDefine.description: Max reserved rate supported by each RPR ringlet. An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in units of 1,000,000 bits per second. If this object reports a value of 'n' then the speed of the interface is somewhere in the range of 'n-500,000' to 'n+499,999'. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth. For a sub-layer which has no concept of bandwidth, this object should be zero.

hh3cRprTopoImageXTable.name: hh3cRprTopoImageXTable
hh3cRprTopoImageXTable.description: This table contains additional objects for the rprTopoImageTable in IEEE-802DOT17-RPR-MIB.

hh3cRprTopoImageXEntry.name: hh3cRprTopoImageXEntry
hh3cRprTopoImageXEntry.description: Each entry contains information specific to a particular station on the ring. The table has at least one entry for the station itself, this entry indicates zero hops on each ringlet.

hh3cRprTopoImageXWestEdgeStatus.name: hh3cRprTopoImageXWestEdgeStatus
hh3cRprTopoImageXWestEdgeStatus.description: The current edge status of the west span. If an edge exists,the hh3cRprTopoImageXWestEdgeStatus is true. Otherwise, the hh3cRprTopoImageXWestEdgeStatus is false.

hh3cRprTopoImageXEastEdgeStatus.name: hh3cRprTopoImageXEastEdgeStatus
hh3cRprTopoImageXEastEdgeStatus.description: The current edge status of the east span. If an edge exists, the hh3cRprTopoImageXEastEdgeStatus is true. Otherwise, the hh3cRprTopoImageXEastEdgeStatus is false.

hh3cRprTopoImageXStationName.name: hh3cRprTopoImageXStationName
hh3cRprTopoImageXStationName.description: The operator assigned station name. The operator can assigned it by hh3cRprTopoImageXStationName.

hh3cRprSrcMacCountTable.name: hh3cRprSrcMacCountTable
hh3cRprSrcMacCountTable.description: The RPR Source Mac Count Table contains the cumulative sum of frames and octects from the particular source station.

hh3cRprSrcMacCountEntry.name: hh3cRprSrcMacCountEntry
hh3cRprSrcMacCountEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Source Mac Count Table.

hh3cRprSrcMacCountIfIndex.name: hh3cRprSrcMacCountIfIndex
hh3cRprSrcMacCountIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of this RPR interface.

hh3cRprSrcMacCountBySrcAddress.name: hh3cRprSrcMacCountBySrcAddress
hh3cRprSrcMacCountBySrcAddress.description: MAC address of the source station where the frames come from.

hh3cRprSrcMacCountReceivedFrames.name: hh3cRprSrcMacCountReceivedFrames
hh3cRprSrcMacCountReceivedFrames.description: Frames received from a particular MAC address of source station.

hh3cRprSrcMacCountReceivedOctets.name: hh3cRprSrcMacCountReceivedOctets
hh3cRprSrcMacCountReceivedOctets.description: Octets received from a particular MAC address of source station.

hh3cRprDestMacCountTable.name: hh3cRprDestMacCountTable
hh3cRprDestMacCountTable.description: The RPR Destination MAC Count Table contains the cumulative sum of frames and octects to the particular destination station.

hh3cRprDestMacCountEntry.name: hh3cRprDestMacCountEntry
hh3cRprDestMacCountEntry.description: An entry in the RPR MAC Destination Count Table.

hh3cRprDestMacCountByDestAddress.name: hh3cRprDestMacCountByDestAddress
hh3cRprDestMacCountByDestAddress.description: MAC address of the destination station where the frames are sent to.

hh3cRprDestMacCountReceivedFrames.name: hh3cRprDestMacCountReceivedFrames
hh3cRprDestMacCountReceivedFrames.description: Frames sent to a particular MAC address of destination station.

hh3cRprDestMacCountReceivedOctets.name: hh3cRprDestMacCountReceivedOctets
hh3cRprDestMacCountReceivedOctets.description: Octets sent to a particular MAC address of destination station.

hh3cRprPktDropCountTable.name: hh3cRprPktDropCountTable
hh3cRprPktDropCountTable.description: The RPR Packet Drop Count Table contains the cumulative sum of packets dropped for congestion.

hh3cRprPktDropCountEntry.name: hh3cRprPktDropCountEntry
hh3cRprPktDropCountEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Packet Drop Count Table.

hh3cRprPktDropCntIfIndex.name: hh3cRprPktDropCntIfIndex
hh3cRprPktDropCntIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of this RPR interface.

hh3cRprPktDropCntRingletID.name: hh3cRprPktDropCntRingletID
hh3cRprPktDropCntRingletID.description: The RPR Ringlet of the station through which the packets transmit.

hh3cRprDownFlowClassAPktDrops.name: hh3cRprDownFlowClassAPktDrops
hh3cRprDownFlowClassAPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class A packets which transmit down from the host.

hh3cRprUpFlowClassAPktDrops.name: hh3cRprUpFlowClassAPktDrops
hh3cRprUpFlowClassAPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class A packets which transmit up to the host.

hh3cRprDownFlowClassBPktDrops.name: hh3cRprDownFlowClassBPktDrops
hh3cRprDownFlowClassBPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class B packets which transmit down from the host.

hh3cRprUpFlowClassBPktDrops.name: hh3cRprUpFlowClassBPktDrops
hh3cRprUpFlowClassBPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class B packets which transmit up to the host.

hh3cRprDownFlowClassCPktDrops.name: hh3cRprDownFlowClassCPktDrops
hh3cRprDownFlowClassCPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class C packets which transmit down from the host.

hh3cRprUpFlowClassCPktDrops.name: hh3cRprUpFlowClassCPktDrops
hh3cRprUpFlowClassCPktDrops.description: The total dropped number of Class C packets which transmit up to the host.

hh3cRprStaticRSTable.name: hh3cRprStaticRSTable
hh3cRprStaticRSTable.description: The RPR Static Ring Selection table contains the static ring selection information by the way of configuration.

hh3cRprStaticRSEntry.name: hh3cRprStaticRSEntry
hh3cRprStaticRSEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Static Ring Selection table.

hh3cRprStaticRSMacAddress.name: hh3cRprStaticRSMacAddress
hh3cRprStaticRSMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the station on the ring.

hh3cRprStaticRSRingletID.name: hh3cRprStaticRSRingletID
hh3cRprStaticRSRingletID.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from one station to another. Ringlet0 refers to outer ring, while ringlet1 does inner.

hh3cRprStaticRSTtl.name: hh3cRprStaticRSTtl
hh3cRprStaticRSTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station by the selected ringlet.

hh3cRprStaticRSValid.name: hh3cRprStaticRSValid
hh3cRprStaticRSValid.description: The flag identify whether the configed ringlet is valid. If it is true, the configed ringlet is valid, otherwise it's invalid.

hh3cRprStaticRSRowStatus.name: hh3cRprStaticRSRowStatus
hh3cRprStaticRSRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The status includes createAndGo, active and destroy.

hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSTable.name: hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSTable
hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSTable.description: The RPR Ipv4Dynamic Ring Selection Table that contains the dynamic ring selection information by shortest path.

hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSEntry.name: hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSEntry
hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Ipv4Dynamic Ring Selection Table.

hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSMacAddress.name: hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSMacAddress
hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSMacAddress.description: The Ipv4 MAC address of destination station on the ring.

hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSRingletID.name: hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSRingletID
hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSRingletID.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from the source station to the destination station.

hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSTtl.name: hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSTtl
hh3cRprIpv4DynamicRSTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station by the selected ringlet.

hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSTable.name: hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSTable
hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSTable.description: The RPR Ipv6 Dynamic Ring Selection Table that contains the Ipv6 ring selection information by dynamic ring selection and static ring selection.

hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSEntry.name: hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSEntry
hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Ipv6 Ring Selection Table.

hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSMacAddress.name: hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSMacAddress
hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSMacAddress.description: The Ipv6 MAC address of the destination station on the ring.

hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSRingletID.name: hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSRingletID
hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSRingletID.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from the source station to the destination station.

hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSTtl.name: hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSTtl
hh3cRprIpv6DynamicRSTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station by selected ringlet.

hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSTable.name: hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSTable
hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSTable.description: The RPR Ipv4 Overall Ring Selection Table that contains the overall and active ring selection infomation by dynamic ring selection and static ring selection.

hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSEntry.name: hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSEntry
hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Overall Ring Selection Table.

hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSMacAddress.name: hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSMacAddress
hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the destination station on the ring.

hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSType.name: hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSType
hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSType.description: The ring selection item type indicates static or dynamic.

hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSRingletID.name: hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSRingletID
hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSRingletID.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from the source station to the destination station.

hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSTtl.name: hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSTtl
hh3cRprIpv4OverallRSTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station by selected ringlet.

hh3cRprVrrpRSTable.name: hh3cRprVrrpRSTable
hh3cRprVrrpRSTable.description: The RPR VRRP Ring Selection Table that contains the ring selection information when the vrrp group is configured.

hh3cRprVrrpRSEntry.name: hh3cRprVrrpRSEntry
hh3cRprVrrpRSEntry.description: An entry in the RPR VRRP Ring Selection Table.

hh3cRprVrrpRSVirtualMacAddress.name: hh3cRprVrrpRSVirtualMacAddress
hh3cRprVrrpRSVirtualMacAddress.description: The virtual MAC address of the staion in VRRP group.

hh3cRprVrrpRSMacAddress.name: hh3cRprVrrpRSMacAddress
hh3cRprVrrpRSMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the station that is the master in VRRP group.

hh3cRprVrrpRSRingletID.name: hh3cRprVrrpRSRingletID
hh3cRprVrrpRSRingletID.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from the source station to the destination station.

hh3cRprVrrpRSTtl.name: hh3cRprVrrpRSTtl
hh3cRprVrrpRSTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station by selected ringlet.

hh3cRprDefaultRingIDTable.name: hh3cRprDefaultRingIDTable
hh3cRprDefaultRingIDTable.description: The RPR Default RingID Table specify the default ringID.

hh3cRprDefaultRingIDEntry.name: hh3cRprDefaultRingIDEntry
hh3cRprDefaultRingIDEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Default RingID Table.

hh3cRprDefaultConfigRingletID.name: hh3cRprDefaultConfigRingletID
hh3cRprDefaultConfigRingletID.description: The default identifier of the ring configured by user.

hh3cRprDefaultActiveRingID.name: hh3cRprDefaultActiveRingID
hh3cRprDefaultActiveRingID.description: The identifier of the default ring which is active currently. The default ring configured by user may be inactive.

hh3cRprDefectReportTable.name: hh3cRprDefectReportTable
hh3cRprDefectReportTable.description: The RPR Defect Report Table that contains the trap information on the ring.

hh3cRprDefectReportEntry.name: hh3cRprDefectReportEntry
hh3cRprDefectReportEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Defect Report Table.

hh3cRprDefectCurrentStatus.name: hh3cRprDefectCurrentStatus
hh3cRprDefectCurrentStatus.description: Indicates the current status of RPR ring. This attribute is used to notify the management system that alarms generate or clear about some RPR ring.

hh3cRprPriority2ClassMapTable.name: hh3cRprPriority2ClassMapTable
hh3cRprPriority2ClassMapTable.description: The Table is for Class Of Service and RPR Service Class Mapping.

hh3cRprPriority2ClassMapEntry.name: hh3cRprPriority2ClassMapEntry
hh3cRprPriority2ClassMapEntry.description: An entry in the COS to Service Class Map Table.

hh3cRprPriority2ClassMapType.name: hh3cRprPriority2ClassMapType
hh3cRprPriority2ClassMapType.description: The type of Priority,include tag, mpls, ip.

hh3cRprPriorityValue.name: hh3cRprPriorityValue
hh3cRprPriorityValue.description: The priority of tag,mpls and ip, the value range is 0~7.

hh3cRprRateLimitConfigTable.name: hh3cRprRateLimitConfigTable
hh3cRprRateLimitConfigTable.description: The RPR Rate Limit Configuration Table that contains the rate limit infomation of RPR serviec class.

hh3cRprRateLimitConfigEntry.name: hh3cRprRateLimitConfigEntry
hh3cRprRateLimitConfigEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Rate Limit Configuration Table.

hh3cRprRateLimitConfigRingletId.name: hh3cRprRateLimitConfigRingletId
hh3cRprRateLimitConfigRingletId.description: The identifier of the ring of RPR ringlet.

hh3cRprRateLimitConfigValue.name: hh3cRprRateLimitConfigValue
hh3cRprRateLimitConfigValue.description: The value of rate-limit that configured for diffrent service class. The unit is permillage.

hh3cRprMacLearnCfgEntry.name: hh3cRprMacLearnCfgEntry
hh3cRprMacLearnCfgEntry.description: The entry of RPR MAC Address Table.

hh3cRprMacLearnRprMac.name: hh3cRprMacLearnRprMac
hh3cRprMacLearnRprMac.description: The MAC address of the RPR station.

hh3cRprMacLearnType.name: hh3cRprMacLearnType
hh3cRprMacLearnType.description: The type of MAC address item that the user built. The type includes static and dynamic.

hh3cRprMacLearnVlanId.name: hh3cRprMacLearnVlanId
hh3cRprMacLearnVlanId.description: The vlan ID that the MAC address learned from by RPR staion.

hh3cRprMacLearnRinglet.name: hh3cRprMacLearnRinglet
hh3cRprMacLearnRinglet.description: The identifier of the ring which frames are sent from the source station to the destination station.

hh3cRprMacLearnTtl.name: hh3cRprMacLearnTtl
hh3cRprMacLearnTtl.description: The hops from source station to destination station on the selected ringlet.

hh3cRprMacLearnIsValid.name: hh3cRprMacLearnIsValid
hh3cRprMacLearnIsValid.description: The flag identify whether the configured mac address is valid. If it is true, the configured mac address is valid, otherwise it's invalid.

hh3cRprMacLearnRowStatus.name: hh3cRprMacLearnRowStatus
hh3cRprMacLearnRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. The status includes createAndGo, active and destroy.

hh3cRprTrapVarTable.name: hh3cRprTrapVarTable
hh3cRprTrapVarTable.description: The RPR Defect Report Table that contains varible that used to bind in trap.

hh3cRprTrapVarEntry.name: hh3cRprTrapVarEntry
hh3cRprTrapVarEntry.description: An entry in the RPR Trap Var Table.

hh3cRprTrapIfIndex.name: hh3cRprTrapIfIndex
hh3cRprTrapIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of RPR interface. It is only used for trap to bind.

hh3cRprTrapRinglet.name: hh3cRprTrapRinglet
hh3cRprTrapRinglet.description: The span of RPR station. It is only used for trap to bind.

hh3cRprTrapTopoMacAddress.name: hh3cRprTrapTopoMacAddress
hh3cRprTrapTopoMacAddress.description: The MAC address of RPR station. It is only used for trap to bind.

hh3cRprTrapIpAddress.name: hh3cRprTrapIpAddress
hh3cRprTrapIpAddress.description: The IP address of RPR station. It is only used for trap to bind.

hh3cRprTopologyOpenRing.name: hh3cRprTopologyOpenRing
hh3cRprTopologyOpenRing.description: The topology openRing trap indicates that the RPR ring is opened.

hh3cRprTopologyCloseRing.name: hh3cRprTopologyCloseRing
hh3cRprTopologyCloseRing.description: The topology openRing trap indicates that the RPR ring is closed.

hh3cRprTopologyInconsistent.name: hh3cRprTopologyInconsistent
hh3cRprTopologyInconsistent.description: The topology inconsistent trap indicates that the topology of RPR is inconsistent.

hh3cRprTopologyInstability.name: hh3cRprTopologyInstability
hh3cRprTopologyInstability.description: The topology instability trap indicates that the topology of RPR is instability.

hh3cRprDuplicateMacAddress.name: hh3cRprDuplicateMacAddress
hh3cRprDuplicateMacAddress.description: The duplicate MAC address trap indicates that the mac address of the station on the ring is dulplicate. That means there is the same MAC address between two stations on the ring.

hh3cRprDulplicateIPAddress.name: hh3cRprDulplicateIPAddress
hh3cRprDulplicateIPAddress.description: The dulplicate IP address trap indicates that the IP address of the station on the ring is dulplicate. That means there is the same IP address between two stations on the ring.

hh3cRprIncompleteLRTT.name: hh3cRprIncompleteLRTT
hh3cRprIncompleteLRTT.description: The incomplete LRTT trap indicates that LRTT is not completed.

hh3cRprProtecConfigInconsistent.name: hh3cRprProtecConfigInconsistent
hh3cRprProtecConfigInconsistent.description: The protection configuration inconsistent trap indicates that the configuration of protection mode on the ring is inconsistent. That is one station is configured steer mode while the other is configured wrap mode.

hh3cRprJumboConfigInconsistent.name: hh3cRprJumboConfigInconsistent
hh3cRprJumboConfigInconsistent.description: The jumbo configuration inconsistent trap indicates that the configuration of jumbo mode on the ring is inconsistent. That is one station supports jumbo frame while the other doesn't support jumbo frame.

hh3cRprExceedMaxReservRate.name: hh3cRprExceedMaxReservRate
hh3cRprExceedMaxReservRate.description: The exceeded max reserved rate trap indicates that the rate on the ringlet exceeded the max reserved rate. The operator can configure reserved rate for every station, but the sum of all stations' reserved rate of each RPR ringlet can't exceed maximum.

hh3cRprExceedMaxStationNum.name: hh3cRprExceedMaxStationNum
hh3cRprExceedMaxStationNum.description: The exceeded max station number trap indicates that the number of the stations on the ring exceeded the max station number.

hh3cRprMiscabling.name: hh3cRprMiscabling
hh3cRprMiscabling.description: The miscabling trap indicates that the miscabling event occurred.

hh3cRprBackPressure.name: hh3cRprBackPressure
hh3cRprBackPressure.description: The back pressure trap indicates that the backpressure is generated on the ringlet. That is the data flow on the ringlet exceeded the range of rate-limit configured.

hh3cRprBackPressureOver.name: hh3cRprBackPressureOver
hh3cRprBackPressureOver.description: The back pressure over trap indicates that the backpressure is disappeared on the ringlet.
